entity.name: Disturbance in Gulf of Mexico officially becomes Tropical Storm Nestor, NHC says
entity.description: The National Hurricane Center confirmed that the developing system in the Gulf of Mexico is now Tropical Storm Nestor. In the report, the NHC warns that "dangerous storm surge and tropical storm force winds [are] expected along portions of the northern Gulf Coast" on Friday.
